    "narrative": "## Rough Night: Model Gets Torched on Unders\n\n**HIGH TIER: 1-1, -4.5% ROI**\n\nThe Detroit-Atlanta over cashed comfortably at 259 despite a modest projection of 232.4, helped significantly by overtime pushing the regulation total to 242. The Dallas-Denver under was a disaster \u2014 projected 236.1, landed at 277. Denver was scoring at an elite rate coming in (117.9 offensive efficiency) but their defense was a sieve (113.7 defensive efficiency), and Dallas somehow found offense despite their poor recent form (105.4 offensive efficiency). The model saw two high-pace teams but completely underestimated how open this game would be.\n\n**MEDIUM TIER: 0-4-1, -80% ROI**\n\nBrutal. Four losses, all unders, all missing badly to the high side.\n\nLakers-Pacers projected 234.7, finished 267. Indiana's defense has been atrocious (118.1 defensive efficiency) and the model knew it, but the 32-point gap suggests both teams shot considerably better than expected in a pace-up environment (104.6 projected).\n\nOKC-Boston under looked solid with Boston's slow pace (95.4) and two elite defenses, but finished 15 points high at 228. No obvious explanation in the pregame data \u2014 this one just got away from us.\n\nMemphis-San Antonio was our only over that lost, and it's the one game where the model was too *high*. Projected 242, finished 221. San Antonio's elite recent offense (120.2 efficiency) completely disappeared, and Memphis's shaky defense (116.8) somehow tightened up.\n\nPortland-Milwaukee projected a glacial 207.8 with two slow-pace teams and poor offenses, but finished at 229. The 21-point miss suggests Milwaukee's offense woke up beyond what their recent 107.7 efficiency indicated.\n\n**LOW TIER: 3-2, +14.5% ROI**\n\nThe only profitable tier on the card \u2014 small sample, but at least something worked.\n\n**WHAT TO WATCH**\n\nSix of seven big misses went over the projection, five of them on under bets. When the model is this consistently low, it's either missing a league-wide pace/efficiency shift or we hit a statistical cluster. Worth monitoring whether defensive intensity is genuinely down across the league right now.",
